  "body": "We currently have `CREATE2` -> `SELFDESTRUCT` in `tests/cancun/eip6780_selfdestruct/test_selfdestruct.py::test_create_selfdestruct_same_tx`, and the self-destructing contract is called several times to do a self-destruct, but we don't have a test that attempts to do `CREATE2` -> `SELFDESTRUCT` -> `CREATE2`.\r\n\r\nWe can improve the test coverage with the following tests:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Perform a `CREATE2`, make sure that the initcode sets at least a couple of storage keys, then on a different call, in the same tx, perform a self-destruct. Then:\r\n  - [ ] a) on the same tx, attempt to recreate the contract\r\n  - [ ] b) on a different tx, attempt to recreate the contract\r\n- [ ] Perform a `CREATE2`, make sure that the initcode sets at least a couple of storage keys, then in a different tx, perform a self-destruct. Then:\r\n  - [ ] a) on the same tx, attempt to recreate the contract\r\n  - [ ] b) on a different tx, attempt to recreate the contract",
